Definition.WordDefinition: Cornfield \Corn"field`\ (k?rn"f?ld`), n. A field where corn is or has been growing; -- in England, a field of wheat, rye, barley, or oats; in America, a field of Indian corn. [1913 Webster]
corn field n : a field planted with corn [syn: {cornfield}]
